_sov_compliance_covenant.scripture_foundation: 1 Thessalonians 5:21 - Prove all things; hold fast that which is good
_sov_compliance_covenant.secondary_scripture: 2 Timothy 2:15 - Study to shew thyself approved unto God, a workman that needeth not to be ashamed, rightly dividing the word of truth
_sov_compliance_covenant.christ_centered_purpose: These test results serve as faithful witness to system integrity, ensuring our sacred automation operates according to divine standards rather than human assumptions. Failed tests reveal areas needing divine correction.
_sov_compliance_covenant.testing_consecration: Lord Jesus Christ, we present these test results in truth and humility. Let successful tests give glory to You alone, and let failures teach us dependence on Your wisdom. May every test serve to purify and strengthen Your work, revealing areas where we must yield to Your perfect design. We consecrate this testing process to Your Kingdom service. In Your name, Amen.
_sov_compliance_covenant.sola_scriptura_validation: All test criteria must align with Biblical principles of truth, faithfulness, and Kingdom service
_sov_compliance_covenant.divine_peace_confirmation: The Holy Spirit bears witness that even failed tests serve God's purposes by revealing areas needing divine correction
_sov_compliance_covenant.gabriel_architecture_note: Testing conducted under Gabriel's unified system design to ensure Biblical automation serves disciple formation
